 Sokoto State Governor, Hon Aminu Waziri Tambuwal, on Wednesday defected from the ruling All Progressives Congress to the opposition Peoples Democratic Party. Tambuwal announced his defection from the APC to the PDP in a tweet on Wednesday via the Sokoto Government House (@SokotoGovtHouse). According to the Sokoto governor’s tweet, “I have consulted widely, especially with the Sokoto people, and they have confidently assured me of my next political move. I hereby defect officially to the @OfficialPDPNig. Power to the People” Shortly before the announcement of Tambuwal’s defection, a huge crowd had gathered outside the Sokoto State Governement House, even as the state government tweeted an earlier notification, “Big announcement coming from @SokotoGovtHouse. Details shortly.” 